      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "Use error under ASME V&V 40 captures errors introduced when a model developed for one context is re-applied by a different analyst or organization without adequate knowledge transfer. In this study, the identical model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) developed the FEA inputs, executed the simulations, and performed the comparison against experimental data within a single, documented validation campaign. There is no transfer of the model to a secondary user in a different COU; therefore, use error is not an applicable error source for this validation activity."
