        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — Gradation 3 minimum",
        "description": "Model form must be justified by comparison to established continuum mechanics theory for metallic implants under quasi-static loading. Isotropic linear-elastic material for Ti-6Al-4V rod and screw body, with bilinear isotropic hardening for post-yield behavior. Contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Gradation 3 requires documented justification of all constitutive assumptions against published literature."
      },
      "rationale": "The constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening, E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.8 GPa for Ti-6Al-4V) is consistent with published material characterization data (ASTM F136, Donachie 2000). Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient μ=0.2 is consistent with metal-on-metal tribological data for Ti-6Al-4V dry contact. Large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM ON) capture the geometric nonlinearity observed in the 40 mm displacement test. Assumptions documented in Model Form Justification Report MFJ-2024-002."
    },
    {
