        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — Gradation 2 minimum, material certs required",
        "description": "All material properties and geometric dimensions must be traceable to either material certification reports or direct measurement of test articles. Gradation 2 minimum; Gradation 3 achieved by including measurement uncertainty propagation through the QoI predictions."
      },
      "rationale": "Geometry derived from CMM measurements of three production screws and rods (mean ± 1σ reported). Material properties sourced from material certification reports for the specific lot of Ti-6Al-4V used in both FEA and bench testing. Torque-to-preload calibration for set-screw tightening documented in Test Protocol TP-2024-003. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=500) to quantify QoI sensitivity to dimensional and material variability."
