        "description": "Gradation 3 requires testing under at least two distinct load configurations (e.g., varying intervertebral distance or offset) to bound the model's predictive range. Gradation 2 achieved with a single standardized ASTM F1717 configuration; offset rationale required for acceptance."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing performed under the single standardized ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration (44 mm intervertebral distance, 10° offset block). Only one test condition was employed due to resource constraints and because the regulatory submission requires only F1717 compliance. This represents a shortfall relative to the Gradation 3 requirement for multiple load configurations. An offset rationale is provided in the DecisionRecord."
