        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria — QoIs directly linked to failure modes",
        "description": "QoIs must be directly linked to the clinically relevant failure modes of the pedicle screw construct. Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are required as they correspond to elastic performance, onset of permanent deformation, and post-yield structural integrity respectively. Gradation 2 minimum; Gradation 3 achieved by documented traceability from QoI to failure mode to clinical consequence."
      },
      "rationale": "Traceability matrix TM-2024-001 maps each QoI to a failure mode: construct stiffness → fatigue life under cyclic loading; yield force → onset of permanent deformation leading to loss of spinal alignment; force at 40 mm → post-yield load-bearing capacity relevant to intraoperative manipulation. Clinical consequence mapping reviewed and approved by clinical affairs team."
