        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria — validation scenario matches COU scenario",
        "description": "The validation scenario (test geometry, loading mode, hardware) must match the COU scenario to Gradation 3: same device design, same loading mode (compression-bending), same ASTM standard (F1717), and same titanium alloy system. Any deviations must be documented and their effect on QoI prediction bounded."
      },
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design, 5.5 mm Ti-6Al-4V rod, and ASTM F1717 test protocol as specified in the COU. No surrogate hardware or scaled geometry was employed. The FEA boundary conditions replicate the F1717 fixture constraints (fixed distal block, displacement-controlled proximal block). Relevance assessment documented in Validation Relevance Report VRR-2024-006."
